GitHub Copilot

Likely causes:
1. Inconsistent auth fetch: Some pages (e.g. qr.html) call fetch('/api/auth.js') without method:'POST' and headers. Server returns 405 → redirect.
2. Reliance only on ?key=… in URL. Fast navigation can drop the param (e.g. intermediate load, cached page, or a link constructed without it) so validation sees no key and redirects.
3. Multiple simultaneous validations: navigating away before a slower failed request completes can still trigger its redirect logic.

Fix strategy (lightweight):
1. Persist key after first successful validation:
   sessionStorage.setItem('authKey', key);
2. Centralize validation in a single JS (e.g. assets/auth-guard.js):
   - Retrieve key = URL param || sessionStorage.getItem('authKey')
   - If missing → login
   - If we have a previously validated key (session flag), skip re‑POST to reduce races.
3. Uniform POST everywhere:
   await fetch('/api/auth.js', {
     method:'POST',
     headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'},
     body: JSON.stringify({ key })
   })
4. Abort stale validations:
   - Keep a validation token (incrementing counter); only act on the latest response.
5. When navigating, always append the key if it’s absent:
   const qs = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
   if (!qs.get('key') && sessionStorage.getItem('authKey')) {
     qs.set('key', sessionStorage.getItem('authKey'));
   }

Sample centralized guard (drop into assets/auth-guard.js and include instead of inline blocks):

(function(){
  let currentRun = 0;
  async function requireAuth() {
    const runId = ++currentRun;
    const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(location.search);
    let key = urlParams.get('key') || sessionStorage.getItem('authKey');
    if (!key) {
      location.replace('login.html');
      return;
    }
    // Skip recheck if already validated this session
    if (sessionStorage.getItem('authValidated') === '1' &&
        sessionStorage.getItem('authKey') === key) return;

    try {
      const res = await fetch('/api/auth.js', {
        method:'POST',
        headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'},
        body: JSON.stringify({ key })
      });
      if (runId !== currentRun) return; // stale
      const data = await res.json();
      if (!data.success) {
        sessionStorage.removeItem('authKey');
        sessionStorage.removeItem('authValidated');
        location.replace('login.html');
        return;
      }
      sessionStorage.setItem('authKey', key);
      sessionStorage.setItem('authValidated','1');
    } catch {
      if (runId === currentRun) location.replace('login.html');
    }
  }

  window.requireAuth = requireAuth;
  requireAuth();
})();

Update navigation (already adjusted):
const qs = params.toString();
location.href = qs ? `/${url}?${qs}` : `/${url}`;

Replace each inline validation block with:
<script src="assets/auth-guard.js"></script>

That removes flicker/redirects on rapid tab switches. Let me know if you want me to apply the changes to all pages.

